Various witnesses have testified that Matshela Koko contributed to Eskom's financial woes. JOHANNESBURG - Matshela Koko is returning to the State Capture Inquiry on Tuesday morning to deliver more Eskom-related evidence. During his last appearance, the former acting power utility CEO told the inquiry the commission must stop targeting him in its investigations in what he called 'The Koko Hunt'. WATCH: Lucky Montana back at state capture inquiry Various witnesses have testified that Koko contributed to Eskom's financial woes. Koko claims their testimony is false and casts him in a bad light.